# ============================================================================
# CONFIGURATION SYSTEM
# ============================================================================
# This project now separates configuration into two layers:
#
# 1. CONFIG FILES (config/config.development.js, config/config.production.js)
#    - Contain non-secret settings such as ports, URLs, feature flags, logging,
#      and performance tuning values.
#    - Tracked in Git for consistency across environments.
#    - Automatically selected based on NODE_ENV.
#
# 2. .ENV FILES (like this one)
#    - Contain *only* secrets: passwords, API keys, tokens, and sensitive URLs.
#    - Never committed to Git. Copy this file to .env and fill in secure values.
#
# Moved to config files: API_GATEWAY_PORT, API_GATEWAY_URL, MAIN_APP_PORT,
# MAIN_APP_URL, FRONTEND_URL, PYTHON_SERVICE_URL, PLUGIN_ENGINE_URL,
# POSTGRES_HOST, POSTGRES_PORT, POSTGRES_DB, REDIS_HOST, REDIS_PORT,
# CORS settings, logging settings, rate limits, upload limits, feature flags,
# analytics toggles, trust proxy, and other non-secret options.
# ============================================================================

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CORE APPLICATION SECRETS
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
JWT_SECRET=REPLACE_WITH_SECURE_RANDOM_STRING_MIN_32_CHARS
SESSION_SECRET=REPLACE_WITH_SECURE_RANDOM_STRING_MIN_32_CHARS
